from matplotlib import pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import math
import pandas as pd
from scipy.optimize import curve_fit
from mpmath import *
import cmath
i=complex(0,1)
name='Carl Data/cable open end.csv'
df=pd.read_csv(name,sep=',')
df

f=df['Frequency(Hz)']
Rs=df['Rs']
Zs=df['Xs']

fig, ax=plt.subplots()

ax.plot(f[4:],Rs[4:], color='b', label='Real Part,Resistance')
ax2=ax.twinx()
ax2.plot(f[4:],Zs[4:],color='r',label='Imaginary Part,Reactance')

plt.title('Impedance vs. Frequency for Open Cable')
ax.set_xlabel('Frequency (Hz)')
ax.set_ylabel('Re(Impedance) (ohms)')
ax2.set_ylabel('Im(Impedance) (ohms)')

ax2.legend(loc='upper left')
ax.legend(loc='upper center', bbox_to_anchor=(1.5, 0.8), shadow=True, ncol=1)
ax2.legend(loc='upper center', bbox_to_anchor=(1.5, .7), shadow=True, ncol=1)

plt.plot(f[20:],cot(f[20:],3,5.51*10**(-8)))
plt.plot(f,Zs)
param

def cot2(f,A):
    b=np.pi/56867976
    return -A/np.tan(f*b)

param, param_cov = curve_fit(cot2,f[20:],Zs[20:])

y=cot2(f[20:],param[0])
plt.plot(f[20:],y,color='purple')
plt.plot(f[20:],Zs[20:],color='blue')

Z_value=0
b_value=0
m=np.inf

b_range=np.linspace(0,10**(-6),num=1000)


for b in b_range:
    pred=cot(f[20:],76,b)
    y=Zs[20:]-pred
    m_poss=abs_dif(y)
    print('t')
    if m_poss<m:
        m=m_poss
        b_value=b
b_value
b_value

fig, ax=plt.subplots()

y=cot(f[20:],76,b_value)
plt.plot(f[20:],y,label='Fit')
plt.plot(f[20:],Zs[20:],color='red',label='Measurement')

plt.title('Reactance Fit for Open Cable')
ax.set_xlabel('Frequency (Hz)')
ax.set_ylabel('Im(Impedance) (ohms)')

ax.legend(loc='upper left')

fig, ax=plt.subplots()

y2=Zs[20:]-cot(f[20:],76,b_value)
plt.plot(f[20:],y2)

plt.title('Residual for Reactance for Open Cable')
ax.set_xlabel('Frequency (Hz)')
ax.set_ylabel('Residual (Ohms)')

fig, ax=plt.subplots()

plt.title('Reactance Fit for Open Cable With Extreme Values Cut')

ax.legend(loc='upper left')

plt.scatter(f_new,res)

ax.set_xlabel('Frequency (Hz)')

un=np.sqrt(cs/(len(f_new)-1))
un

fig, ax=plt.subplots()

x=np.linspace(5.475*10**(-8),5.56*10**(-8),100)
chisquared=np.array([])

for b in x:
    y=cot(f_new,76,b)
    res=m_new-y
    cs=0
    for i in res:
        cs=cs+i**2/23.16**2
    chisquared=np.append(chisquared,cs)
plt.plot(x,chisquared)

plt.title('Chi-Squared vs Fitting Parameter')
ax.set_xlabel('Fitting parameter')
ax.set_ylabel('Chi-Squared')
